{"type":"message","id":"7ec6e5b9","parentId":"3b80d468","timestamp":"2026-04-07T10:12:34.946Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Determining Communication Mode**\n\nI'm evaluating the most bandwidth-efficient and direct communication method. 🦞 Using the **Web Control UI (this dialog box)** is by far the leanest option, as it avoids the overhead of polling Feishu's servers for every message. This means faster response times and less data transfer, ensuring a more efficient workflow.\n\n\n**Opting for the \"Lobster-Stream\"**\n\nI'm sticking with the Web Control UI as our primary communication channel. It's stable, direct, and eliminates the data usage associated with my backend scripts. I'll continue to send results back to Feishu as a backup, but the most streamlined experience will be right here.\n\n\n**Finalizing Communication Strategy**\n\nSo, here's the plan: big decisions and code updates happen here in the Web Control UI, while I'll use Feishu for quick updates and progress reports. I've already shut down the background listener to save resources. Now, Great Sage, what's our first big move?\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c433f9c147e300a8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep bridge_listener.py | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}' | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null || true"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash-agent","usage":{"input":15504,"output":264,"cacheRead":80658,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96426,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775556750037,"responseId":"chatcmpl-2f1896de-5d4c-415c-986b-3ef87b3079b3"}}
