{"type":"message","id":"dff4640f","parentId":"f7318cfc","timestamp":"2026-04-07T10:22:28.076Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Resolving Plugin Initialization Error**\n\nI'm seeing a \"TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'specifier')\" in my logs. 🦞 I've decided to abandon the `defineBundledChannelEntry` wrapper since it might be expecting something I'm not providing. Instead, I'll export a standard plugin object with `register` and `activate` functions. This should fix the issue and get the Feishu channel up and running.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5df2d33b697bbc89","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"export async function register(api) {\n  const { registerFeishuChannel } = await import(\"./channel-entry.js\");\n  return registerFeishuChannel(api);\n}\n\nexport async function activate(api) {\n  const { activateFeishuChannel } = await import(\"./channel-entry.js\");\n  return activateFeishuChannel(api);\n}\n\nexport default {\n  id: \"feishu\",\n  name: \"Feishu\",\n  description: \"OpenClaw Feishu/Lark channel plugin\",\n  register,\n  activate\n};\n","path":"/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/index.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash-agent","usage":{"input":16499,"output":267,"cacheRead":80608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97374,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775557343405,"responseId":"chatcmpl-967162b1-38d3-4c0d-b8ef-54198942088f"}}
